{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandate a national referendum for any petition reaching 1 million signatures",
        "additional_details": "Currently, petitions reaching 100K signatures can only lead to a debate, often leading to no action from the Government. We think a 1m signature threshold represents a huge mandate that deserves a binding vote. Residents with settled status (ILR/EUSS) pay taxes and are permanent members of our society; they must have a say in major national changes. To manage costs (historically \u00a375m\u2013\u00a3130m per vote), referendums should be bundled into one annual \u201cDecision Day\u201d or held during elections. We think this would turn the petitions site into a tool for real democratic change.",
        "background": "Introduce legislation to require a national referendum for petitions with 1m+ signatures, open to UK citizens and residents with settled status.",
